I love Potbelly's. I've been to at least 10 different ones in the Chicagoland area--including the original on Lincoln ave. that my mom used to live above when she was in medical school--but this is my favorite. The staff at most potbellys are nice, but these guys take it to the next level, being equally amusing and friendly. My boyfriend complained about how the friendly banter delays service sometimes, but I think that's the charm inherit to Potbelly's. And if it takes me an extra minute to get a wreck sandwich w/ everything on it and a chocolate shake, I am totally okay with that. Only complaint: be open for breakfast.

I love potbelly but this location lacks speed. I used to work at a busier location than this. I won't stop coming to potbelly, just keep in mind there not as quick. 5 stars for quality 1 1/2 for staff. Wish I could see their mystery shopper review
